metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #30
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.

metadata.name: Vents #551
metadata.description:
Near the start of December @Studio Yorktown launched his "Studio Yorktown Color Town Hall" library of wonderful colour palettes.

"You know what this Town Hall needs?" I asked no one in particular, "Vents!". Besides, what's more Christmassy than a good old vent?

Some nice soothing gradients, with a selection of innies and outies, structure, form, and sometimes sharp edges. I humbly suggest aiming to get a set of three üòÅ

Thank you for everything fxhash in 2022, looking forwards to 2023!

READ MORE: https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/vents

INSTRUCTIONS ::

h - Toggle high-res
n - toggle noise on/off
s - Download and save image

PRINTING INSTRUCTIONS ::

High-res will output a 8,192 x 8,192 image, at 300dpi it should print at...

27.3 x 27.3 inches
69.3 x 69.3 cm

metadata.name: Bankoo #35
metadata.description:
The word affects and reshapes land in an eternal cycle.

The development of this series invited me to cross the land through songs and glyphs and to discover the Manding languages script: N'Ko. It is a cables.gl patch that blends procedural terrains and text strings made from 8 letters whose order is continuously randomized (it takes some time, be patient).

The piece has some controls:
- Use 1, 2, 3 and 4 to change the view.
- Use P to open the performance panel.
- Use S to download a black and white image of the terrain to use as height map or to hear it using PIXELSYNTH (https://ojack.xyz/PIXELSYNTH/)

A more detailed article about this artwork can be found here: https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/bankoo-or-nko-or-u%2B07c0-u%2B07ff ‚õ∞Ô∏è

metadata.name: gimme all your love #141
metadata.description: Sometimes we feel so lost that we look for any way to find the ground beneath our feet again. Sometimes we try to feel something through other people, through looks, words, touches. This is a temporary cure, which sooner or later will stop helping.

metadata.name: STRUCTURES #86
metadata.description:
STRUCTURES

What color do things look when you're happy?

First of all I want to dedicate this collection to all the people who paint their emotions with color, who through a chromatic range, are capable of feeling a universe of sensations most of the time inexplicable.....

 I am fascinated by how generative art creates a perfect symbiosis between art and technology, allowing through a set of algorithmic rules to give rise to compositions where shapes and colors coexist in balance, harmonized with each other that give rise to new creations.

This collection is designed to be self-contained and limited, recreating the view from different angles and phases of the day that can lead to disparate interpretations of a piece.

My work as a visual artist explores elements such as randomness and chance of linear formations and geometric gradients that broaden the spectrum to increasingly new concepts that I definitely want to explore.

I continually wonder what the geometric patterns that will emerge from my sensibility will be like and will give rise to new collections like this one, which is why I continue to investigate techniques and shapes while having fun.

"A painting is not the image of an experience, but it is the experience." Mark Rothk

metadata.name: k3rnel #144
metadata.description:
Self-organizing future-jazz geometry for like-minded pixel based neighbourhoods. 


********
Glossary
********

'Self-organization' ‚Üí the process by which individuals organize their communal behaviour to create global order by interactions amongst themselves rather than through external intervention or instruction.

'Future-jazz-geometry' ‚Üí propulsive syncopated visual rhythms, polyphonic ensemble playing, varying degrees of improvisation, and often deliberate distortions of pitch and timbre.

'Like-minded' ‚Üí sharing the same opinions, ideas, or interests. 

'Pixel' ‚Üí the smallest addressable element in an all points addressable display device; so it is the smallest controllable element of a picture represented on the screen.

'Neighbourhood' ‚Üí a spatial unit, in which face-to-face social interactions occur.

Touch to listen, go fullscreen

metadata.name: little god #73
metadata.description:
All of our strong emotions, feelings and experiences come from childhood. Sincere happiness or frightening cruelty is primarily inherent in children, so they learn about the world. When we were children, we first hurt someone, first burst into tears from resentment, learned what is good and what is bad. 
Our parents did not answer our questions, either because they did not know the answer or because they thought we were too young. We learned to look for the answers ourselves. Whoever says that children don't understand is a fool. They do understand, but they do it in their own way. The world as seen through the eyes of a child is not like the world as seen through the eyes of an adult. It is often not built on the laws of physics or the laws of the marketplace. In a child's world or universe, the moon is just a little light in the sky, and the next street is already a different country. Their world is built on speculation and magical theories. Unfortunately, a child's world is not eternal. As they grow up, the "real" life, the life of adults, pokes into them like a sharp needle over and over again. 
There is something incredibly tragic about this time gap between child and adult. It is this period that I wanted to trace in my work. As teenagers, it is as if we are between two trains, we are no longer children, but we are not yet adults. We get to know ourselves, we test our strength and readiness to exist in the "real" world. We are trying to find our place in the unfriendly world of adults, but we are also not ready to let go of the magic of childhood. It confuses, torments, and frustrates us. But it is a necessary and unavoidable tragedy. 

Code by PureSpider

metadata.name: Shine On #119
metadata.description:
You enter a room, bathed in light
Where a beautiful sculpture takes your sight
Shimmering in the glow of the sun
It's a sight to behold, it's simply won

Remember when you were young
You shone like the sun
Your radiance filled the room
With a feeling of pure bloom

Your heart sings, a soul takes flight
As you stand in awe, all worries take flight
Shine on you crazy diamond, bright and true
Your radiance fills the room, your heart anew

metadata.name: WTBS: Olympics Poster Edition #7
metadata.description:
WTBS: Olympics Poster Edition is our official collaboration with Jeres, who was kind enough to work with us in support of the show. The project leans into classic Olympic poster design motifs, embellished by Jeres' signature approach to color and shape. Huge thanks to Jeres for donating their time and enthusiasm to this one, we hope you enjoy it!

As with all WTBS projects, your minting will directly support the podcast and keep us going (and more importantly, collecting!). Our goal is to keep the show free from ads and fully supported by the community, your donations and contributions continue to make that possible. Thank you in advance to everyone who chooses to mint!

Jeres: I love vintage posters. When going to second-hand shops, flea markets or wherever people are selling their used goods, I‚Äôm always on the lookout for what people used to hang on their walls. Bauhaus-inspired posters, socialist propaganda, Nagel prints, anything art deco, etc.. but whenever I come across something Olympics inspired I always feel like I hit pay dirt. There‚Äôs something about the clean, simple design being used to show people coming together along with the undertones of human excellence that just feels special. And circles. I love circles. I hope you enjoy this collection as much as I enjoyed putting it together with Trinity and Will.

Approximate rarity notes:
5%: Gold Edition
10%: Silver Edition
15%: Bronze Edition

metadata.name: Another Perspective #2 #158
metadata.description:
This work was made using reverse perspective projection.
Perspective projection is common in traditional Western painting and 3D computer graphics.
However, it is not always necessary to use it, as in this work.

Drag the screen to change the camera angle.

Made with Three.js
